"text":"Pub. L. 94–106, § 814(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/540"},"text":"89 Stat. 540","children":[],"tail":"; restated "},{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"July 14, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/361/s802"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–361, § 802","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/930"},"text":"90 Stat. 930","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"2457(f)","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"10:2451 (note).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Aug. 5, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/365/s302/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–365, § 302(c)","children":[],"tail":" (4th sentence), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/402"},"text":"88 Stat. 402","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the introductory matter of subsection (a), before clause (1), the word “equipment” is substituted for “impedimenta” in section 302(c) of the Department of Defense Appropriation Authorization Act, 1975 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/365"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–365","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/402"},"text":"88 Stat. 402","children":[],"tail":"), for clarity and for consistency with section 814(a)(1) of the Department of Defense Appropriation Authorization Act, 1976 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/106"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–106","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-10-07"},"text":"Oct. 7, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/540"},"text":"89 Stat. 540","children":[],"tail":"), which is restated as part of this subsection."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(1), the word “undertake” is omitted as surplus. The word “members” is substituted for “countries” for consistency. The words “including the United States” are omitted as unnecessary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(2), the words “The Secretary of Defense shall also” are omitted as unnecessary. The word “maintain” is substituted for “develop” because it is more appropriate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(3), the words “of other members of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization whenever such equipment is to be used by personnel of the Armed Forces of the United States stationed in Europe under the terms of the North Atlantic Treaty” are omitted as unnecessary because of the restatement. The words “Such procedures shall also take into . . . to be procured” are omitted as unnecessary. The text of section 814(a)(1) (4th, last sentences) is omitted as executed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “It is the sense of the Congress”, “It is further the sense of Congress”, “It is the Congress’ considered judgment”, “properly”, “Accordingly”, and “pursuant to these ends” are omitted as unnecessary.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c)(1), the word “should” is substituted for “shall” for clarity.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(1), the word “members” is substituted for “allies” for consistency. The words “The Secretary of Defense shall include in the report to the Congress required by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/365/s302/c"},"text":"section 302(c) of Public Law 93–365","children":[],"tail":", as amended” are omitted as unnecessary because of the restatement."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(2), the words “The report required under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/365/s302/c"},"text":"section 302(c) of Public Law 93–365","children":[],"tail":" shall include” are omitted as unnecessary because of the restatement."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(3), the words “he shall report that fact to the Congress in the annual report required under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/365/s302/c"},"text":"section 302(c) of Public Law 93–365","children":[],"tail":", as amended” are omitted as unnecessary because of the restatement."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(4), the words “The Secretary of Defense shall, in the reports required by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/365/s302/c"},"text":"section 302(c) of Public Law 93–365","children":[],"tail":", as amended” are omitted as unnecessary because of the restatement."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(5), the words “if none exist” are substituted for “In the absence of such common requirements” to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “the Secretary shall include a discussion of the” are omitted as unnecessary because of the restatement.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(6), the words “The Secretary of Defense shall also report on” are omitted as unnecessary because of the restatement.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(7), the words “those programs” are substituted for “all such existing and planned programs” and “all such programs” to eliminate unnecessary words.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (f), the words “The Secretary shall submit the results of these . . . to Congress” are omitted as unnecessary because of the source provisions restated in subsection (d)(1). The word “submit” is substituted for “cause to be brought” to eliminate unnecessary words. The words “in order that the suggested actions and recommendations can” are omitted as unnecessary because of the restatement.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida978c203-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida978c204-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2011—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/350"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–350","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s8302"},"text":"section 8302 of title 41","children":[],"tail":"” for “section 2 of the Buy American Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s10a"},"text":"41 U.S.C. 10a","children":[],"tail":")”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/136"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–136","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsec. (d) which related to Secretary’s biennial submission of report to Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106","children":[],"tail":" substituted “the Buy American Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s10a"},"text":"41 U.S.C. 10a","children":[],"tail":")” for “title III of the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1933-03-03"},"text":"March 3, 1933","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s10a"},"text":"41 U.S.C. 10a","children":[],"tail":"),”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/510"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–510","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-02-01"},"text":"February 1, 1989","children":[],"tail":", and biennially thereafter” for “Before February 1 of each year”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
